            <p class="desc_2">Pi (<span class="pi">&pi;</span>) is the ratio of a circle's circumference to its diameter, a fundamental constant in mathematics. It is approximately 3.14, an irrational number with an infinite, non-repeating decimal sequence. Calculators show Ï€ as 3.141592654 due to their 10-digit display limit, although it's commonly approximated as 3.14 or <sup>22</sup>/<sub>7</sub> </p>

        
            

            
            <div class="spacer_3 layer_3 flip"></div>
        </section>
    </main>








        <footer class="footer">

            <p>Made by BVIS students</p>

        </footer>
    

    <script type = "module" src="/js/home.js"></script>
    <script type="module" src = "/js/logOut.js"></script>
</body>

